      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Your students should frame strict enforcement as the only way to end the current \"death trap\" reality, where uncontrolled crossings force families into life-or-death choices at the border. By arguing that the current chaotic system is inherently inhumane because it prioritizes quantity over safety, they can position a controlled, orderly process as the true moral imperative that saves lives. This approach shifts the debate from a political preference to an ethical necessity, proving that order and compassion are not mutually exclusive but rather foundational to human rights.",
      "source": "target",
